flowRoot.flowPara: Specifically php typed objects that Group together fields. They are used to store & display structured data (eg nodes, comments, taxonomy terms etc).
An Entity Bundle is a certain kind of an entity type like a "sub-type". It's like an interface for a php class.
A field is a reusable way to enter, store, and display information on the site, such as text, dates, and numbers.
A node is somehow like an instance of a specific Bundle. It has a unique ID, data values & other fields or settings inherited from its (parent) Bundle.
Unique configurations attached to each Bundle that allows site builders to easy manage the UI (widgets, grouping, show off etc) of the Entity submit form.
Similar to Form Modes but for rendering fields. Typical display modes are Full Content, Teaser, Search index, RSS etc.
